  "texts": [
    "Now compare this with the artificially intelligent poll provided by YouGov in this constituency the very same year.",
    "Their MrP model was able to estimate a new prediction every day between the 4th of December and the 10th of December (two days before the election), leveraging a national sample of 105, 612 respondents, recruited from an online panel.",
    "The final published MrP predictions for Guildford were substantially more accurate giving the Conservatives a 5% lead-a much closer call to the observed 5.7% lead in favour of the Conservatives, who won the seat.",
    "Had you, hypothetical voter, been aware of these results, you might have decided to vote for your actual preference, the Labour candidate, and avoid the moral cost of voting tactically.",
    "The normative significance of traditional opinion polls in times of election has been often neglected and sometimes criticised."
  ],
